3:37 Defendant David J Zabawa in court with attorney Gary J. Kryshak.  Defendant David J Zabawa in custody.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
David Bailey is sworn as a witness and questioned by Attorney Lambert. He is a police officer with the Wisconsin Rapids Police Department. On 9/8/15, he talked to R.N. who stated that firearms and weapons were stolen from a safe in his home. He stated he was out of town for the previous 3 days. R.N. had suspected someone. He spoke to several witnesses who stated the defendant was involved in the incident. They stated that the defendant sold the firearms. The witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom. Attorney Kryshak cross-examines witness. 
Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and the defendant committed it. Bound over for further proceedings. Bond is continued.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 18, 2016 at 09:00 am.
